We've integrated @projectsigstore support for container image signing into the GitHub Actions starter workflow, so that developers can sign their container images by default. Check out the details!
Hack to avoid self-closing empty div, do not remove
Safeguard your containers with new container signing capability in GitHub Actions | The GitHub Blog
GitHub has partnered with the OpenSSF and Project Sigstore to add container image signing to our default “Publish Docker Container” workflow, giving your users confidence that the container images they got from their container registry was the trusted code that you built and published.
